Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Halve the @red chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded, finely chopped), then finely chop. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(halved, zest reserved).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Crumble half the @Greek style salad cheese{100%grams} into a #medium bowl{}. Add the chilli (add less if you'd prefer things milder), peanuts, half the coriander and half the garlic.

Add the @olive oil for the salsa{1%tbsp} and squeeze in half the lemon juice. Stir together and set aside.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated), then coarsely grate (no need to peel). Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Add the sweetcorn to a #blender{}. Blend the sweetcorn until finely chopped, ~{1-2%mins}.

In a #large bowl{}, add the @plain flour{100%grams} and @water for the fritters{3/4%tsp}. Stir in the blended corn and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in the carrot and crumble in the remaining cheese. Add the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and the remaining coriander and remaining garlic. Stir together until well combined.

Heat a #large frying pan{} to medium-high heat with enough @olive oil{} to coat the bottom.

Once hot, place heaped tablespoons of the fritter mixture (in batches) into the pan. Flatten slightly with the back of your #spoon{}, then fry until golden and cooked through, ~{3-4%mins} each side.

> TIP: Don't flip them too early, they need time to set.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Keep cooking in batches until all the mixture is used up - you should get 3-4 fritters per person.

> TIP: Add extra oil in between batches if needed.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed and leaves separated), separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces. Cut the @medium tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks) into 1cm chunks.

In a medium bowl, combine the @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} with the remaining lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's nearly ready, add the lettuce and tomato to the dressing bowl. Toss to evenly coat.

Share your fritters and wedges between plates.

Sprinkle the lemon zest over the wedges. Spoon the salsa over the fritters.

Serve with the baby gem and tomato salad on the side.

Enjoy!